article.description: — Kyrell Luc had a season-high 24 points as Holy Cross snapped its nine-game road losing streak, narrowly defeating Boston University 75-70 on Monday night.
article.headline: Luc scores 24 to carry Holy Cross past Boston U. 75-70
article.linkText: Luc scores 24 to carry Holy Cross past Boston U. 75-70
article.story: BOSTON -- — Kyrell Luc had a season-high 24 points as Holy Cross snapped its nine-game road losing streak, narrowly defeating Boston University 75-70 on Monday night. Bo Montgomery had 16 points and six rebounds for Holy Cross (5-15, 3-5 Patriot League). Malcolm Townsel added 12 points. Caleb Kenney had 2 points and five blocks. The Crusaders swatted a season-high 10 blocks. Javante McCoy had 18 points for the Terriers (15-9, 6-5), whose four-game win streak ended. Sukhmail Mathon added 14 points and 10 rebounds. Walter Whyte had 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
